<div style="font-family:Jost, monospace; color:#e0e0e0; font-size:18px; line-height:1.65;">
<center><font size="9"> [General Description] </font></center>
{{Background|file=Level 827, darkest staircase..png}}


{{Blurimage|file=Level 827, darkest staircase..png|caption=“Where does it lead??”}} 
'''Level 827, also known as "The Party Is Dead," is a dimly lit environment resembling a suburban household from the 1980s. Darkness is constantly present throughout the level, with only a limited number of functioning light sources providing visibility. The house appears larger on the inside than expected, containing multiple connected hallways, small rooms, storage spaces, and an upstairs floor that shares the same architectural style as the ground level.'''

'''Various party-related items can be found scattered throughout the level, usually placed on tables, inside drawers, or left on the floor. These items appear to originate from a celebration that was never completed or was suddenly abandoned. Common objects include party hats, decorative streamers, paper plates, wrapped boxes, balloons, and board games. Cakes are also frequently found, though they appear artificial and cannot be safely consumed. Many decorations appear faded or slightly damaged, contributing to the quiet and somewhat unsettling feeling present throughout the level.'''

'''The walls are typically covered in faded wallpaper, often featuring simple patterns or soft colors that have slightly deteriorated over time. Wooden furniture is present in most rooms, including cabinets, drawers, tables, and shelves. Despite signs of age and abandonment, the structure itself remains stable, with no visible signs of collapse or severe structural damage.'''
{{Blurimage|file=Level 827 rewrite.jpg|caption=“Something Is Lurking In The Darkness”.}} 
'''Lighting within the level is limited and mainly provided by old ceiling lamps, table lamps, and occasional decorative lights. Wanderers often report feeling calmer when standing near these lamps, as the lighting creates a welcoming atmosphere despite the overall emptiness of the house. However, areas outside the reach of these lights are often extremely dark, making it difficult to see clearly and increasing the chance of disorientation.'''

'''Bookshelves are one of the most useful features of Level 827. These shelves often contain survival guides, journals, and file folders describing other levels of the Backrooms. The information found in these books usually ranges from [[Level 0]] up to [[Level 827]]. Many of the documents contain details about environmental dangers, known entities, entrances, exits, and useful survival advice. The accuracy of the information is generally considered reliable, making bookshelves valuable resources for wanderers attempting to safely explore other levels. Some books appear old and worn, while others look relatively new, suggesting that the collection may update over time.'''

'''The temperature within the level generally remains stable at approximately 18.7 °C (65.6 °F), though small variations can occur depending on the room. Some areas may feel slightly warmer or cooler without any clear reason. Despite the comfortable temperature, the environment often feels emotionally cold due to the absence of activity or visible life.'''
<center><font size="9"> [Locations/Sections] </font></center>
<div style="background:#a1a1a1; border:2px solid black; color:white; padding:2em;">
{{Collapse|initial=<big><big><center>'''The attic'''</center></big></big>|final=<big><big><center>'''The attic'''</center></big></big>|num=0|body=
<br>
----
'''The attic is a smaller and less frequently explored area located above the main upper floor of Level 827. It can usually be accessed through a narrow staircase or a ceiling hatch found in certain rooms. The Attic has a noticeably lower ceiling than the rest of the level. Wooden support beams are visible throughout the space, and the floor is typically covered in dust and small debris.'''
{{Blurimage|file=Level 827 rewrite 3.png|hovertext=An image of the Attic.|alt=An image of the Attic.|caption=An image of the Attic|align=center}}
'''Various old objects are scattered across the Attic, including sealed boxes, broken furniture, old toys, and damaged party decorations. Some containers may hold books, photographs, or other small items, though many appear empty or deteriorated. The area is usually poorly lit, with only weak light coming from small lamps or faint light sources from below. Shadows often form between the wooden beams, making visibility inconsistent in certain sections.'''

'''The atmosphere within the Attic is quiet and slightly uncomfortable, often producing subtle sounds such as wood creaking or objects shifting without clear cause. While the Attic is generally not considered as dangerous as the basement, wanderers are advised to remain cautious, as the confined layout may make movement difficult if a Blackout occurs. The Attic is often avoided unless necessary, due to its limited space and unclear purpose within the level.'''
</div>}}

<div style="background:#a1a1a1; border:2px solid black; color:white; padding:2em;">
{{Collapse|initial=<big><big><center>'''The basement'''</center></big></big>|final=<big><big><center>'''The basement'''</center></big></big>|num=1|body=
<br>
----
'''The Basement is considered the most dangerous area of Level 827 and is strongly avoided by most wanderers. It is typically accessed through a wooden door located somewhere on the Ground Level, often near the kitchen or in a hallway corner. The staircase leading downward is narrow and poorly lit, with the light becoming weaker the further one descends. In many cases, the Basement appears almost completely dark, even when other parts of the level still have functioning lamps.'''
{{Blurimage|file=Level 827 rewrite 4.jpg|hovertext=An Image of the basement.|alt=An Image of the basement.|caption=An Image of the basement.|align=center}}
'''The Basement is believed to be the primary location where several hostile entities reside, including the Uninvited. Under normal conditions, these entities rarely leave this area, though their presence can sometimes be detected through distant sounds such as slow footsteps, faint knocking, or the movement of objects. The layout of the Basement is unclear, as very few wanderers have explored it fully and returned safely. Reports suggest the area contains multiple small rooms, tight corridors, and storage-like spaces filled with old furniture, boxes, and damaged party-related objects.'''

'''The environment within the Basement feels significantly more oppressive than the rest of the level. The air often feels heavier, and the silence is occasionally interrupted by unexplained noises. Light sources are extremely limited, and some lamps found in the Basement may flicker or fail entirely. Because of the confined spaces and lack of reliable lighting, navigating the Basement can be very disorienting.'''

'''During a Blackout event, the Basement becomes especially dangerous, as entities contained within it are able to move freely throughout the house. The Uninvited is believed to emerge from the Basement when this occurs, making entry into this area extremely risky even outside of Blackouts. Wanderers are strongly advised to avoid the Basement whenever possible, as it offers very few benefits and presents a high risk of encountering hostile entities.'''
</div>}}
