<center><font size="7"> [Environment/Events] </font></center>
==Blackout==
'''Blackout is a rare but extremely dangerous event in Level 827 in which all active light sources suddenly stop functioning without warning. Ceiling lamps, table lamps, televisions, and other sources of light will immediately shut off, causing the entire house to become almost completely dark. Visibility during a Blackout is extremely limited, making movement through hallways and rooms very risky. Areas that normally feel safe can quickly become hazardous once darkness takes over the level.'''
{{Blurimage|file=Level 827 rewrite 2.jpg|caption=“What Just Happend???”.}} 
'''During a Blackout, entities normally confined to the basement are able to roam freely throughout the house. The most dangerous of these entities is known as The Uninvited. This entity is highly aggressive and will actively hunt any wanderer it detects. The Uninvited will attack on sight and moves quietly through the level, often approaching without being noticed until it is already very close. Because of the near-total darkness present during a Blackout, wanderers may only hear faint footsteps, subtle floor creaking, or distant movement as warning signs of its presence.'''

'''The only reliable way to survive a Blackout is to hide or barricade yourself inside a room before The Uninvited reaches your location. Blocking doors using heavy furniture or other objects may prevent the entity from entering. Wanderers should remain as quiet as possible, as loud sounds or sudden movement can easily reveal their position. Attempting to explore the level during a Blackout is extremely dangerous and often leads to fatal encounters. Preparing a safe hiding location before a Blackout occurs can greatly increase survival chances.'''

'''Blackouts typically last between several minutes and one hour. Once the event ends, all light sources will begin functioning again, and The Uninvited will stop hunting before eventually returning to the basement. Wanderers are strongly advised to remain cautious even after the lights return, as the entity’s behavior is not fully understood. Remaining prepared and aware of surroundings is essential for surviving repeated Blackouts in Level 827.'''
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}


<center><font size="7"> [Entities & Dangers] </font></center>
==The Uninvited==
{{Entity Class|Agg=5|Int=4|Dan=5|no=???|Hab=Only confirmed in [[Level 827]]}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level 827 rewrite The Uninvited.png|caption=“Only confirmed picture of the Uninvited”.}} 
'''The Uninvited is a tall humanoid entity believed to measure between 2.2 and 2.6 meters (7.2–8.5 ft) in height. Its body appears unnaturally thin, with long limbs and slightly hunched posture, likely due to the low ceilings found in certain areas of Level 827. Witnesses often describe its movements as slow but deliberate, with minimal sound produced while walking.'''

'''The entity is most commonly seen standing near doorways, at the end of hallways, or partially visible on staircases. It rarely makes sudden movements unless it has already detected a wanderer. Its exact facial features are unclear, though some reports mention faint reflective points resembling eyes when observed in extremely low light.'''

'''The Uninvited is believed to have a strong awareness of the layout of Level 827. It appears capable of navigating the house without hesitation. In several reports, the entity has been observed stopping outside closed doors for extended periods of time, possibly listening for movement inside.'''

'''Due to the Uninvited frequently hunting other entities within the Basement, mainly Smilers and Skin-Stealers, encounters between these entities are uncommon in other parts of Level 827.'''


<center><font size="7"> [Colonies & Outposts] </font></center>
'''Due to the level’s hostile conditions, constant darkness, and the presence of dangerous entities, no colonies or permanent outposts have been successfully established within Level 827.'''
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

<center><font size="7"> [Entrances and Exits] </font></center>
==Entrances==
*'''Finding a certain book on [[Level 442]] and destroying it may lead to Level 827.'''
*'''Opening certain doors in [[Level 960]] has a chance of leading here.'''
*'''Entering a beige door on any party-themed level may lead to Level 827.'''
*'''Reading a book in [[Level 540]] titled "The Party Is Already Dead" will lead one here.'''

==Exits==
*'''Finding a white invitation on a wooden table has a high chance of leading to [[Level 799]].'''
*'''Finding a manhole cover in the bathroom and opening it has will lead to [[Level 883]].'''
*'''Walking far enough into the basement section without dying will eventually lead to [[Level 997]].'''
*'''Smashing the toilet in the bathroom has a low chance of leading to [[Level 655]].'''
*'''A red staircase (which has a 9% chance to happen) may appear at any time. Going up the stairs will bring you into a studio room. You will collapse on the floor and wake up in [[Level 930]]'''.
